<br>
Problem is, in the time the Fire pet casts a spell (that may be resisted!) ..ANY other pet would have gotten off 1 or 2 melee rounds and in each of those melee rounds could be quad hits for 58 dmg apeice. I even started killing &quot;greens&quot; to compare the damage of the 51 earth pet to the 52 fire pet.....51 earth pet kills the target faster EVERY time. From the original EQ i thought Fire pets were supposed to have the highest damage output because of the weakest hit points. It seems to me they simply have lowest hp and lowest dmg output.<br>
<br>
I have talked to several other mages about this issue including some that were level 60. Had a 60 mage tell me he still uses the 49 Fire pet when a fire pet is needed (fighting something that uses AE fire). I think it's simply sad when a 60 mage even &quot;thinks&quot; about using a 49 fire pet when he &quot;should&quot; be using the 58 fire pet.<br>
<br>
I am not the most experienced mage out there, as I said only level 52 atm, but from my experiences I think the 50+ fire pets should be modeled as the 49 fire pet only bigger DS, hit harder, and bigger fire nukes, and of course higher level. Please post if you agree or disagree about this and why.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 2:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=780.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   50+ pets</span><hr size=1> It seems like the Voc and Greater Voceration pets (except maybe earth) are really geared towards group situations, which does not seem to bode well for solo players such as myself.  The Voc fire pet is supposed to do a good job of stunning, so maybe it would be a good idea to go back to the idea of heavy nuking of mobs instead of letting pet solo mob down to low hps and then blasting to finish off the kill (at least that's how I solo). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loraffthemage>Loraff the Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 10:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=780.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   50+ fire pets</span><hr size=1> I seldom (maybe twice) use the 50+ fire pets either.<br>
<br>
Many of the mages here seem to have epic pets, with a great built-in DS, so there won't be much posting for the VFire and GVFire to be changed.  Those &quot;wizard&quot; pets do have uses which have been discussed plenty of times (some really like the chain-stunning fire pet and they just re-summon till they get it) but they just don't seem to be very satisfying.<br>
<br>
Verant has responded to things like this before by simply providing an alternate version of a spell, but leaving the original alone.  ie: they could easily create a Voc. &amp; GVoc. Fire melee-style variation and put them on the gnome merchant in the bazaar with a different name, or rename the ones we have like they did with the Rod of Mystical Transvergence .<br>
<br>
It would be nice if the Fire summons were the melee type, and the wizard pet was modelled after something different looking, maybe a djinn or a big eye.<br>
<br>
For the many mages without an epic pet this would offer a nice continuation of the self-ds'g fire pets used through 49th, and leave the wizard pets in the game for the people who like to use them.<br>
<br>
Loraff<br>
56 Mage<br>
Forgotten Guard, Emarr<br>
